# GitHub Packages configuration.
#
# If your project depends on private packages hosted on GitHub Packages,
# uncomment and update the lines below to configure the registry and
# authentication. This file contains no credentials and is safe to commit.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Registry
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# @your-github-org:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Authentication
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Authentication is required to install private packages from GitHub Packages.
# Choose ONE of the following approaches:
#
# Option 1 (recommended) — Global ~/.npmrc
#   Add the following line to your global ~/.npmrc file (~/.npmrc, not this
#   file). This keeps credentials out of any project directory entirely:
#
#   //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=your_github_token_here
#
# Option 2 — Environment variable
#   Uncomment the line below and export NODE_AUTH_TOKEN in your shell profile
#   (e.g. ~/.zshrc or ~/.bashrc):
#
#   export NODE_AUTH_TOKEN=your_github_token_here
#
# ⚠️  NEVER hardcode a token in this file. This file is committed to version
#     control. Tokens must live in ~/.npmrc or your shell environment only.
#
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NODE_AUTH_TOKEN}
